					<td valign="top">
<B CLASS="HeadlineText">This Love Has Taken It's Toll on Me (Tradeskills Hurt!)</B><BR><BR><P>By Lillianan Fuzziebunnie</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;It’s been brought to my attention that EverQuest will soon be implementing a <A href="http://www.rpgexpert.com/1010.html">new tradeskills interface</A>. Personally as a tradeskill nut, I love this idea. Those of the weary wrist will apparently have less combines to click. I’ve always felt that the tradeskill system in game to be cumbersome and painful but it always seemed to be an excellent way to spend time in game while I wasn’t raiding as well as a nice source of money. There will apparently no longer be the need to constantly window out for recipes and my notebook of recipes can gladly be tossed out the window. I’m sure there will be much rejoicing if the interface works well.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>As to site news the Spell Listing is almost complete and I’m slowly filling in quests that might be relevant. I am still looking for help in regards to writing out some of this information as there is a ton of stuff that would be useful here on site. If you would like to offer suggestions or help (my inbox is a bloody mess) then please let me know <A href="http://pub150.ezboard.com/feqhunterfrm12.showmessage?topicid=74.topic">here</A>.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><o:p>&nbsp;The plot of the strange "Yantis and IGE buying everything in site" (pun intended) drama seems to get thicker as it was announced&nbsp;on Thursday that </o:p>Internet Gaming Entertainment ltd. or IGE is acquiring all of Yantis’ assets. Both IGE and Yantis are known to sell items, characters and EverQuest cash for profit. Mr. Yantis will be joining IGE as Chief Operating Officer and a member of IGE Board of Managers. Results of this business transaction are yet to be seen in the community if any are to be seen at all beyond several of the well liked class communities shifting to other locations. Discussion of this tidbit of information can be seen <A href="http://pub150.ezboard.com/feqhunterfrm13.showmessage?topicid=19.topic">here</A>.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>On Tuesday, January 27th, at 10:00 AM GMT (02:00 AM PST) SoE will be bringing the EverQuest servers Antonius Bayle and Venril Sathir down for network maintenance. The estimated downtime is 2 hours.</P>
<P style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="COLOR: black"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>We’re still taking parses on site so please contact Specki or Pharstar for information. Be sure to disclose information such as: Primary, Secondary, ATK, Haste, Combat Effects, Accuracy, and anything else that you think may affect the results.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR clear=all>
